Because it is not possible to traverse all the tree structures, constructing a decision tree based on space division is an NP problem. XGBoost uses a greedy algorithm to traverse the segmentation points of all features in the CART regression tree and calculates the gain before and after the segmentation point to determine whether a node continues to grow. The node will split when the value of the objective function after splitting is higher than the gain of the single-leaf node. At the same time, the maximum depth of the tree and a threshold should be set to limit its growth. The gain formula is shown in formula (14):14\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
